Reasoning: The paper proposes a deep learning approach for solving the classification problem of self-care problems in physically disabled children. This involves the use of autoencoders and deep neural networks, which are commonly used in the fields of artificial intelligence and machine learning (cs.AI, cs.LG). The study also involves the use of a real-world dataset and a conceptual framework designed by the World Health Organization, which could fall under the categories of cybernetics (cs.CY) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper involves the classification of textual data, which could also fall under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL).
